@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy | ToolNexus";
    ViewData["Description"] = "Read how ToolNexus handles privacy and data in plain language, including what is collected and what to avoid sharing.";
    ViewData["CanonicalUrl"] = $"{Context.Request.Scheme}://{Context.Request.Host}/privacy";
    ViewData["Keywords"] = "ToolNexus privacy policy, developer data handling, platform privacy";
}

<article class="static-page legal-page page-shell" aria-label="ToolNexus privacy policy">
    <header class="static-page__header">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p>Short version: I don't want your private data, and you should not treat ToolNexus as a vault. This page explains exactly what happens around data.</p>
    </header>

    <nav class="static-page__section static-page__nav" aria-label="Privacy quick links">
        <h2>Related legal pages</h2>
        <ul class="static-page__link-list">
            <li><a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a></li>
            <li><a href="/cookie-policy">Cookie Policy</a></li>
            <li><a href="/contact-us">Privacy questions</a></li>
        </ul>
    </nav>

    <section class="static-page__section">
        <h2>What data is used</h2>
        <p>Tool input is used to perform the action you requested, like formatting or conversion. If you paste text into a tool, that text is processed so the output can be generated.</p>
        <p>Operational data may also be collected, such as page hits, tool usage counts, error rates, and response timing. This helps debug issues and keep the platform stable.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="static-page__section">
        <h2>What not to upload</h2>
        <p>Please do not paste passwords, private keys, API tokens, medical records, or customer secrets.</p>
        <p>If you need to test with real-world structures, use redacted or synthetic samples.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="static-page__section">
        <h2>How long data is kept</h2>
        <p>Where temporary server-side records exist for reliability or abuse prevention, retention is limited and tied to operational needs.</p>
        <p>We do not sell your data or build personal profiles for ad targeting.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="static-page__section">
        <h2>Security and third parties</h2>
        <p>ToolNexus uses standard infrastructure providers for hosting and delivery. Those providers may process technical metadata needed to run the service.</p>
        <p>No system is perfect, so treat this platform like any normal developer utility: useful, but not a place for highly sensitive information.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="static-page__section">
        <h2>Your controls</h2>
        <p>You control what you submit. The easiest privacy win is simple: only share the minimum data needed for the task.</p>
    </section>
</article>
